article.description: — Corey Washington scored 19 points as Saint Peter's beat Marist 69-60 on Sunday night.
article.headline: Washington leads Saint Peter's to 69-60 victory over Marist
article.linkText: Washington leads Saint Peter's to 69-60 victory over Marist
article.story: JERSEY CITY, N.J. -- — Corey Washington scored 19 points as Saint Peter's beat Marist 69-60 on Sunday night. Washington had five rebounds for the Peacocks (15-11, 11-6 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Roy Clarke added 12 points and Marcus Randolph scored 11. Jackson Price had 12 points to lead the Red Foxes (15-10, 10-6), who had a five-game win streak come to an end. Josh Pascarelli added 11 points. Jaden Daughtry had nine points and 16 rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
